@flexiarg relationship-coherence/base-camp
@title Offer Your Place as the Shared Hub
@sigils [🏠/巢]
@keywords base-camp, hub, hospitality, stashed-key, guaranteed-entry, home-away, futon, provisions
@audience correspondents meeting near-daily under real logistics
@references [relationship-coherence/capacity-honoring relationship-coherence/cook-as-care relationship-coherence/low-pressure-bid]
@references-extra ["Instance of origin: 2026-05-09 — Joe, 'please come to my place as a base camp when you're ready!' Reinforced 2026-05-11 (stashed house key in a 'hidey hole' for 'guaranteed entry' while he's away) and run both ways across May-June (bag/bike deposited, key returned to the secret spot)."]
@tone practical
@style pattern

! conclusion: When one of you is burdened, travelling, or depleted, offer your own place — flat, office, futon, provisions, a stashed key — as a shared hub the other can land in without friction.

  + context: Two self-directed lives meeting most days need somewhere to rest, work, and store a bag between excursions. The relationship acquires physical infrastructure: a home base, guaranteed entry, a fluffed futon kept ready.

  + IF:
    the other needs a place to nap, work, drop a bag, or shelter, and getting all the way home would cost more than it's worth.

  + HOWEVER:
    a hub only works if entry is genuinely frictionless (a real key, a known spot) and the offer is standing rather than case-by-case; a grudging or conditional base is no base at all.

  + THEN:
    make your space available on standing terms — 'come as a base camp', a key in the hidey-hole, the futon kept ready — so the other can arrive, rest, and let themselves in.

  + BECAUSE:
    a shared hub converts two separate territories into one inhabitable field; guaranteed low-friction landing is a daily, material form of welcome.

  + NEXT-STEPS:
    - Pair with relationship-coherence/capacity-honoring (the hub is where rest actually happens) and relationship-coherence/cook-as-care (the hub is where food gets made).
